  "prompt": "How do you cook cube steak?",
  "response": "Here are a few ways to cook cube steak:\n\n1. Pan-frying method:\n- Dredge steak in seasoned flour\n- Heat oil in a skillet\n- Cook 3-4 minutes per side until golden brown\n- Can add gravy after cooking\n\n2. Oven-baked method:\n- Coat steak in breadcrumbs or flour\n- Place on baking sheet\n- Bake at 350\u00b0F for about 20-25 minutes\n- Flip halfway through cooking\n\n3. Slow cooker method:\n- Brown steak in pan first\n- Place in slow cooker\n- Add gravy or cream of mushroom soup\n- Cook on low for 6-8 hours\n\n4. Stovetop smothered method:\n- Brown steak in skillet\n- Remove meat\n- Saut\u00e9 onions in same pan\n- Add meat back with gravy\n- Simmer until tender (about 30-45 minutes)\n\nTips:\n- Cube steak is tough, so cooking low and slow helps tenderize it\n- Use a meat mallet to further tenderize before cooking\n- Season well with salt, pepper, and herbs\n- Don't overcook to prevent becoming tough",
